Shareholders of FCMB Group Plc  have  unanimously approved the payment of a cash dividend of 14 kobo per ordinary share, which translates to N2.77 billion for the investors for the year ended December 31, 2019. The shareholders  gave the approval at the 7thAnnual General Meeting (AGM) of the Group on April 28, 2020 at its corporate head office in Lagos. They also commended the financial institution for its resilience, dynamism and impressive performance recorded last year despite the challenging operating environment. The AGM was streamed live on the bank’s website following the current COVID-19  pandemic and the lockdown of the economy. Presenting the report for the year ended December 31, 2019, the FCMB Group Chairman, Mr. Oladipupo Jadesimi, stated that all the three business groups within FCMB Group Plc reported improved performances, in terms of higher earnings and profits, compared to what was achieved in 2018. On his part, the National Chairman, Progressive Shareholders Association of Nigeria, Mr. Boniface Okezie, said, “FCMB Group performed very well in the financial year ended December 31, 2019. The result is encouraging, and dividend is growing. We urge the Board, Management and Staff to continue in this positive direction. We look forward to see more value and gains this year”. FCMB shareholders  commend  higher dividend declaration FCMB sustains performance with N177.4bn revenue, achieves 73% profit increase FCMB Group reports N188bn revenue, N20.1bn profit